AFRICAN HORSE SICKNESS - ZIMBABWE
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 2 Oct 2004
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information 1 Oct 2004 Vol. 17 - No. 40 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec1>

African horse sickness in Zimbabwe
See also: 13 Jun 2003
(Date of previous outbreak of African horse sickness in Zimbabwe reported
to the OIE: May 2003).
Extract from the monthly report of Zimbabwe for August 2004, received from
Dr Stuart K. Hargreaves, Director of Veterinary Services, Ministry of
Agriculture, Harare:
Location No. of outbreaks in August 2004
Matabeleland South (in the southern part of the country) 1
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species: equ
susceptible : 4
cases: 1
deaths: 1
destroyed: 0
slaughtered : 0
Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department: The Delegate of
Zimbabwe to the OIE has been requested to provide more information on the
outbreak.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It appears as if AHS is more widespread this year than in previous years.
Does anyone know whether my impression is correct? Any well-accepted
explanation for the apparently increased level of AHS disease? - Mod.PC]
